	baddWKv5zQ [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="green" WIDTH="150"><B>Rule</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">But the mere purchase for money of the<BR ALIGN='left'/>assets of one Company by another is<BR ALIGN='left'/>beyond the evident purpose of the<BR ALIGN='left'/>provision, and has no real semblance to<BR ALIGN='left'/>a merger or consolidation. Certainly, we<BR ALIGN='left'/>think that to be within the exemption<BR ALIGN='left'/>the seller must acquire an interest in<BR ALIGN='left'/>the affairs of the purchasing company<BR ALIGN='left'/>more definite than that incident to<BR ALIGN='left'/>ownership of its short-term purchase-<BR ALIGN='left'/>money notes.&quot; And we now add that this<BR ALIGN='left'/>interest must be definite and material;<BR ALIGN='left'/>it must represent a substantial part of<BR ALIGN='left'/>the value of the thing transferred.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
