  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="lightblue" WIDTH="150"><B>Analysis</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">True it is that the relationship of the<BR ALIGN='left'/>taxpayer to the assets conveyed was<BR ALIGN='left'/>substantially changed, but this is not<BR ALIGN='left'/>inhibited by the statute. Also, a large<BR ALIGN='left'/>part of the consideration was cash.<BR ALIGN='left'/>This, we think, is permissible so long<BR ALIGN='left'/>as the taxpayer received an interest in<BR ALIGN='left'/>the affairs of the transferee which<BR ALIGN='left'/>represented a material part of the value<BR ALIGN='left'/>of the transferred assets.</TD></TR>
